    "As the library primarily focuses on data solutions, two distinct scenarios were tested in the high-level users' context: user load testing within the server-to-peer scenario and data transferring throughput in the peer-to-peer scenario.",
    "The application involved in the server-to-peer case conducted smart data transmission of various data types, including netCDF, GRIBB, TIFF, and HDF5 files.",
    "Figure 8 shows the workflow following the case study.",
    "These files ranged in size from 1MB to 2.6GB.",
    "The primary objective of the load testing was to stress the server and assess its behavior under increasing client requests, considering the current hardware limitations."
